    A collection of objects arranged in a nested structure: hashMap K1, hashMap pair K2, hashSet. It is extremely efficient to look for an object of type E if K1 and K2 are attributes of E This nested collection has a tiered structure as follows: A HashMap at top tier (TIER_0) with instances of type K1 as keys paired with values of type HashMap The nested HashMaps inside TIER_0 constitute the tier (TIER_1). Each element of TIER_1 HashMaps has keys of type K2 paired with a value of type HashSet. The HasSet is of type E
